            . I am a <rs id="t18220522-17-viclabel89" type="occupation">builder</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220522-17-victim179 t18220522-17-viclabel89"></join>; I live in Gray's-inn Lane. On the 26th of April, about twelve o'clock, I was in a court in <placeName id="t18220522-17-crimeloc90">Little Moorfields</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18220522-17-crimeloc90" type="placeName" value="Little Moorfields"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18220522-17-crimeloc90" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220522-17-off87 t18220522-17-crimeloc90"></join> - I felt a motion at my coat pocket, put my hand behind but perceived nothing. Immediately after the prisoner ran from behind me; I then missed my handkerchief and pursued him for a quarter of a mile, and only lost sight of him in turning the corner; I secured him in Fore-street, and found my handkerchief in his hat.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220522-17-person181">
                  BARTHOLOMEW 
                  WOOD
               <interp inst="t18220522-17-person181" type="surname" value="WOOD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220522-17-person181" type="given" value="BARTHOLOMEW"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220522-17-person181" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I took him in charge, but found nothing on him.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. A mob stood by a farrier's shop; I went up the court and picked up the handkerchief.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18220522-17-verdict91" type="verdictDescription">
